Otherwise, if there are objects in existence but you wish to start a new
one, you can ask 3-Demon to create a new object with either the New or
New Child commands in the Object menu. The New command creates an 
object that is at the same position in the object HIERARCHY as the currently
selected object. The New Child command creates an object that is the child
of the currently selected object. In either case, the newly created object
becomes the selected object and you are now free to edit it.

Notice that objects created with the New and New Child commands have
a small gray triangle in the top left corner of the view. This provides a
handle on this object, since without any triangles or lines there would be
no way to select this object for any of the operations in the Object menu.

