position is its name, as in the above example.

If an object is the child of another object, the parent's name is first, followed
by a slash, followed by the child object:

This scheme is very much like what we use to describe directories and
subdirectories in AmigaDOS. As we move down the tree, each object is separated
by a slash, just as when moving down a directory tree from the top.

To change the position of an object in the HIERARCHY, simply edit it to reflect
