Select the file you wish to open. For more on using the file file requester, see
the chapter The File Requester.

				86

The object will be loaded and a second requester opened:

You are given several options. If the CENTER command is selected, the object
will be shifted to the center of the view. This is done not by moving all of
the points in the object, but by creating a transformation that shifts them
instead. See the chapter Transforming an Object if you are unsure about
transformations. Later, you can make the centering permanent by invoking the
CONVERT command in the transformation window for this object.

If the SCALE command is selected, a transformation that expands or shrinks the
object to fit the view is created.

Finally, the third command, ADD,  creates a back face triangle for every triangle
in the object. This doubles the size of the object but guarantees that you see
the entire thing.

It's usually a good idea to sue the CENTER and SCALE commands, they position and
scale the object so it is immediately easy to work with.

If you are feeling lazy and would rather not flip the back faces (gwan, getta job
